[1] Nigeria
Date: Tue 14 Feb 2006
From: "Mary Marshall" <tropical.forestry@btinternet.com>
Source: Reuters Foundation AlertNet, Tue 14 Feb 2006 [edited]
<http://www.alertnet.org/thenews/newsdesk/L14373066.htm>

Nigeria: Children Not Infected by Avian Influenza virus
-------------------------------------------------------
Two Nigerian children suspected of having [contracted] avian
influenza probably did not have the virus after all, health officials
said on Tuesday [14 Feb 2006]. "They had a fever and were not
infected by the bird flu virus. They have been treated and are now
okay," said permanent secretary of the Health Ministry in the
northern state of Kaduna, Abdulhamid Abubakar, a medical doctor. If
the children had contracted the disease, they would have been the
first humans known to be infected in Africa.
--
